          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What format works best for how-to content?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>The best format depends on the platform and the complexity of the task. Blog posts optimise for organic search and featured snippets. Instagram carousels drive saves and shares. Short-form videos on TikTok and Reels perform well for visual tasks. The same how-to topic can and should be repurposed across formats — write the blog post first, then adapt it into a carousel, then a short video.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How long should a how-to blog post be?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Most how-to blog posts perform well at 1,000-2,000 words, adjusted for task complexity. A simple topic like "how to write a bio" may need only 800 words. A technical topic like "how to set up Google Analytics 4" may need 2,500 words to cover all edge cases and screenshots. Match depth to the task, not to an arbitrary word count target.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Should you give away all your expertise in how-to content?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Giving away expertise in how-to content builds authority, not competition. Most readers who consume a how-to article will not self-execute the task — they will hire someone who clearly knows what they are talking about. For service businesses, generous educational content is one of the highest-ROI marketing investments because it demonstrates expertise at scale.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Does how-to content earn featured snippets?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
